import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['open'] = pd.to_numeric(data['open'], errors='coerce')
    plt.hist(data['open'], bins=20, color='blue', edgecolor='black')
    plt.axvline(data['open'].mean(), color='red', label='Mean: {:.2f}'.format(data['open'].mean()))
    plt.axvline(data['open'].median(), color='green', label='Median: {:.2f}'.format(data['open'].median()))
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of opening prices?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data = data.sort_values(by='date')
    plt.plot(data['date'], data['close'])
    plt.title('What is the trend of closing prices over time?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    plt.scatter(data['open'], data['close'])
    plt.title('What is the correlation between opening and closing prices?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Opening Price')
    plt.ylabel('Closing Price')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['ret'].plot(kind='hist', bins=20, color='blue', edgecolor='black')
    plt.axvline(data['ret'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean = {data['ret'].mean():0.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['ret'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median = {data['ret'].median():0.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of returns on investment?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['signal'].value_counts().plot(kind='bar')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of signals?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
